1 (2) THE LEGISLATIVE BODY OF THE COUNTY WHERE THE FACILITY IS
2 LOCATED OR THE BALTIMORE CITY COUNCIL, IF THE FACILITY IS LOCATED IN
3 BALTIMORE CITY; AND
4 (3) THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OF THE COUNTY WHERE THE FACILITY IS
5 LOCATED OR THE MAYOR OF BALTIMORE CITY, IF THE FACILITY IS LOCATED IN
6 BALTIMORE CITY.
7 (B) THE NOTIFICATION REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
8 SECTION:
9 (1) SHALL INCLUDE THE CAUSE OF DEATH OF THE DECEASED
10 INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL; AND
11 (2) MAY NOT INCLUDE PROTECTED HEALTH INFORMATION OF THE
12 DECEASED INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL.
13 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS COMPLIANT WITH THE
14 FEDERAL HEALTH INSURANCE PORTABILITY AND ACCOUNTABILITY ACT TO
15 IMPLEMENT THIS SECTION.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
17 October 1, 2025.

